==English==

===Etymology===
From latin "-opticon" for "[[observe]]" and "pan-" for "all".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}} 
'''panopticon'''
# a type of [[prison]] designed by [[philosopher]] Jeremy Bentham wherein all the [[cells]] are visible from the center of the building.
